				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$FIR=Aexp[\frac{-{\rm{\Delta }}{E}_{f}}{KT}]+B$$\end{document}where A is a fitting constant, B is the overlapping of fluorescence peaks, ΔEf is the fitting energy difference between the two thermally couples levels, K is Boltzmann’s constant and T is absolute temperature.

